gomodel:SYNGO_1787  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 4F, Fig. 5C and E, GSK3b staining is conspicuously present on the postsynaptic density.\n\nLiteral:\n\"In the neuropil, dense immunolabeling was found in postsynaptic densities in both dendrites and dendritic spines.\"\n\"Figure 5. ... C) A labeled astrocytic process (a) is surrounding an unlabeled blood vessel (v). The basement membrane and endothelial cell are devoid of labeling. A dendrite (d) and a postsynaptic density (white arrowhead) are also labeled. Note that myelin is completely devoid of immunostaining (black star). ... E) Examples of two synapses. One is a GSK3b-labeled synapse (white arrowhead), while the other synapse is unlabeled (black arrowhead).\". Experimental description: Mouse brains are used for the immunohistochemistry and electron microscopy experiments.\n\nLiteral from M6M\n\"Immunohistochemistry Six adult male C57BL6 mice (10 to 12 week old) were used in this study.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1787" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

